                <div class="views-slideshow-cycle-main-frame-row views_slideshow_cycle_slide views_slideshow_slide views-row-4 views_slideshow_cycle_hidden views-row-even" id="views_slideshow_cycle_div_splash_image-block_1_3">
                 <div class="views-slideshow-cycle-main-frame-row-item views-row views-row-0 views-row-odd">
                  <div class="views-field views-field-body">
                   <div class="field-content">
                    <p>
                     This conference explored the intimate relations and tensions that accrue between Hebrew, Yiddish, and German. The keynote address was delivered by Liliane Weissberg, the Christopher H. Browne Distinguished Professor in Arts and Sciences and Professor of German and Comparative Literature at the University of Pennsylvania. See the conference schedule and participants
